 This trial was made up of two stages with different designs and was conducted at two clinical trial sites.

 Stage I was open-label and uncontrolled in a small cohort of women (n=6) to obtain first experience in employing Org 36286 in women meeting all inclusion and none of the exclusion criteria.

 Based on the results of a previous study, the most appropriate dose was anticipated to be 120 1/2g Org 36286, which was administered on Cycle Day 2 or 3.

 After seven days, treatment was continued with a fixed dose of 150 IU Puregon(R) SC.

