25 mg Orgalutran(R) SC once daily was administered concurrently with 150 IU Puregon(R) up to and including the day of hCG.

 The maximum total treatment duration was 19 days.

 Treatment of the first two participants with Org 36286 120 1/2g, that was expected to be adequate for COH, was cancelled due to disrupted follicular growth beyond Day 7.

 Therefore, the dose of Org 36286 was adapted from 120 1/2g to 180 mu g.

 Treatment of the first participants gave an indication of the validity of the anticipated doses to be used in Stage II, the actual dose-finding trial.

 Stage II was open-label, prospective and randomized, comparing three experimental regimens differing in dose of Org 36286 (120 1/2g, 180 1/2g, or 240 1/2g) with a reference treatment.

 Post-treatment assessments were completed at the visit two weeks after embryo transfer.

